8, 400 passengers between Friday and Monday, every week from the end of November, 2012 until February, 2013.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	I had spent the previous nine years in Canada as a lumberjack, sawing railway ties for the American and Canadian railways and exporting timber to Japan. When I left Canada to escape the winter and to pay a brief visit to the family back home, I had no idea that visit would change my life forever. And so began a new career&hellip;a love affair with the sea, ships and shipping, which I am still passionate about and still doing 30 years on. There were many challenges, adventures, triumphs and disasters over the years but, looking back, it has been a wonderful experience working together with my brother, Clifford, and sister, Daphne, in the same company&hellip;building what is now a huge, unmatched local cruise industry.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	Exciting times, I must say, but the future looks equally as challenging and exciting with bigger ships and longer seasons envisaged for the future. With cruising recognised as the fastest growing sector of the travel industry worldwide, MSC Starlight Cruises is perfectly positioned to ensure that South Africa does not lag behind.</font></p>', 'opera, love, affair, challenges, passionate', '2012-04-27 07:24:50', NULL, 'false', 7);
